replies.body:
It's a pretty useful item on {{champion:9}} ... I know, few play him live ergo nobody plays him on PBE, but it's just so good on him: it offers mana, CDr, tankyness, and damage amp, all stats that Fiddle loves.
Will you keep an eye on Fiddle too? Please?

{{sticker:cass-cry}}

Mage supports have expensive builds because they are APCs disguised as a support with a sightstone item (RIP) They need to get kills/assists to keep up in gold and remain relevant which is why they don't see as much play, because they aren't as consistent.

Most supports who forgo support items do so at a lower level of play, where throws, comebacks, and longer games are more common.  More kills = more gold.  At a higher level melee supports will go {{item:3097}} {{item:3190}} {{item:3109}}  and shielding supports will go {{item:3305}} {{item:3504}} {{item:3107}} 

its all about gold relevance, so they go with the less costly support items with powerful actives to remain relevant.
